## Exercise Types Reference

### Material Providers (Input Phase)
- **text-passage**: Reading content for comprehension
- **audio-clip**: Listening material (requires audio file)
- **video-content**: Video material (requires video file)
- **image-prompt**: Visual prompts for description/discussion

### Assessment Types (Comprehension Phase)
- **multiple-choice**: Questions with 4 options, 1 correct answer
- **true-false**: Statements to evaluate as true or false
- **fill-blanks**: Sentences with missing words to fill in
- **sequencing**: Items to arrange in correct order

### Production Types (Output Phase)
- **short-answer**: Open-ended questions requiring brief responses
- **summary-writing**: Summarize a text or topic
- **opinion-writing**: Express and justify an opinion
- **discussion-prompt**: Questions for discussion/reflection
- **description-writing**: Describe something in detail
- **dictation**: Listen and write what you hear (requires audio)
- **role-play**: Act out a scenario (for speaking practice)
- **sentence-completion**: Complete partial sentences
